subj.title:
Also without any thermometer it would be clear that the Earth is warming. Just look at sea ice, sea level rise, melting glaciers, later river freezing, earlier ice breakup, earlier spring and animal migration, movement of animals, plants, insects and ecosystems towards to poles and up mountains, etc.

These chances can be used for independent warming estimates. [See for example this one for glaciers](http://dx.doi.org/10.1126/science.1107046) or this study [estimating warming via the time rivers and lakes freeze up.](http://dx.doi.org/10.1126/science.289.5485.1743)
Image of the Week – Breaking the ice: river ice as a marker of climate change
